props.name: Find a YouTube app that summarizes and extracts facts.
Develop a podcast player that summarizes and extracts facts.
A podcast player that slows down during complex speech.
Nodes matching a tag in Tana are synced to Anki.
Given a tag XYZ, display the name of each node tagged with XYZ.
The meta node has children. One of these children will be the ID of a tag.
A node that is tagged has a _metaNodeId attribute.
"Nodes matching a tag" has an id of `t6FdGHdpLARW`.
`F9-0KeWo0Ylw` has children, and one of the children is the outcome ID.

Data could be entered into Obsidian. Notes with a particular type are synced to Anki, linking back to the note. Anki simply contains a link to the note and does scheduling. All activities like extraction are done within Obsidian, which syncs new extractions back to Anki.
Actually doing work that is text based.
AI Subconscious -> Objective Consciousness -> Human Consciousness -> Human Subconscious.
Influencing the human performing the work.
Influencing the algorithm based upon mood.
Chaining semantically similar work across different topics.
Suggestions for breaking down outcomes into smaller outcomes.
Supermemo / Incremental Reading approach to life outcomes.
Just like you can have different decks in Anki, you could have separate "decks" that map to contexts, like leisure time, software dev, career development, etc.
Ability to see the entire tree's contents at a glance.
Time spent could alternate between planning in near-realtime and executing (synthesizing).

A human should be able to provide feedback in realtime to influence the algorithm. You see something and want to work on it again soon, point it a 5, if you don't want to see it for a long time, point it a 1.
Outcomes can often be broken down into smaller outcomes.
After you take massive action, you need to utilize sensory acuity.
After you know why you want it, you need to take massive action.
But it is not enough to just know the outcome, even though that sets you apart from the herd. Next, you need to know why you want it.
I was listening to Tony Robbins earlier today. He talked about how we need to be outcome oriented. In any given situation, we should be asking ourselves repeatedly "what is my desired outcome?".
I have enough time for my mental and physical health, and for others.
Every moment should be utilized effectively, even driving in the car. Videos and materials can be summarized and repeated at decaying intervals.
Life is like an RPG. I have 5 year, 3 year, 1 year goals, which get broken down into objectives and tasks. In any given moment, I know where I stand in relation to my standards.
Every output I make, whether it is notes, code contributions, Wiki updates, or something else, enters into a pipeline, branching through different states until it is finished or reincorporated.
I know where all of my time goes. I can review my time spent and categorize it based on tags.

I wake up in the morning full of energy. I know exactly what to do, and in what order to do it. I don't need to think about any aspect of my day, the algorithm tells me what to do, and I'm provided with frequent motivational feedback.

Block based systems are powerful. They mimic the way my mind works, with the ability to narrow focus repeatedly, to write an atomic thought that has its own metadata separate from the rest of the document.
Frequent positive feedback throughout the day helps keep me on track.
Linking anger and pain to negative outcomes and pleasure and gratitude to positive outcomes works.
Systems that have a lot of friction don't get used as often. I need to account for fluctuations in my mental state.
In the past I have planned too much into the future and the plans did not stick.
Weekly objectives provide comfort and help me to focus on the right things.
I feel best when I have a target and my daily activities align with the targets.
Substances can accelerate productivity, but they come at a net-negative cost.
I've been thinking lately about what my next system might look like. I still feel that it is possible to design a system that propels me towards the future that I desire.
